item.title: Project Insanity Help
item.dc:creator: @purestmage74 purestmage74
item.description:
@purestmage74 wrote:

You can actually see the exact character that it’s pointing to (Character meaning letter/number).

public static ZombieCaves zombiecaves = new ZombieCaves();

It’s pointing to the Z in ZombieCaves, ZombieCaves is the name of the class file.
Look around in the files, if there isn’t a file called ‘ZombieCaves.java’, than there’s your error, you’re trying to compile a class it cannot reach.

I’ll help ya just:
F33D M3 INFO
F33D M3 CODE

item.title: Project Insanity Help
item.dc:creator: @purestmage74 purestmage74
item.description:
@purestmage74 wrote:

Replace that line with:

public static ZombieCaves zombiecaves = new ZombieCaves();

If it’s still giving a error, go check in the ZombieCaves file, if the Constructor of the file says:

public ZombieCaves(Client c) {
}

Than you’ll have to replace your error with the peram ‘this’.

public static ZombieCaves zombiecaves = new ZombieCaves(this);

EDIT: nevermind, just seen the compiling error is coming from MiniGames.java, so don’t use the = new ZombieCaves(this);
use the first line i posted.

Your only mistake was from using ’ <> ’ when it should of been ’ () ’
